    <section>
      <h2>Typical deal scenarios</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Italian industrial groups acquiring Spanish companies or business units</li>
        <li>Spanish businesses entering or expanding into the Italian market</li>
        <li>Joint ventures between Italian and Spanish partners</li>
        <li>Transactions where real estate is a material component of the deal</li>
        <li>Post-acquisition reorganisations and integrations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Issues frequently encountered in Italy–Spain M&amp;A</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Different approaches to risk allocation and deal certainty</li>
        <li>Governance structures, minority protections and deadlock mechanisms</li>
        <li>Formalities, powers of attorney and notarial requirements</li>
        <li>Timing mismatches between signing and closing</li>
        <li>Negotiation dynamics and cultural expectations</li>
        <li>Post-closing corporate housekeeping across jurisdictions</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
